docs.abstract: Be it objectification or celebration, the annual rite she created earned millions for the magazine and helped usher in the supermodel era.
docs.snippet: Be it objectification or celebration, the annual rite she created earned millions for the magazine and helped usher in the supermodel era.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jule Campbell, the mastermind of the Sports Illustrated swimsuit issue, the annual paean to cheesecake — or healthy celebration of female beauty and athleticism, depending on your point of view — that broke publishing records and helped usher in the era of the supermodel, died on Nov. 19 in Flemington, N.J. She was 96.

headline.main: Jule Campbell, 96, Dies; Architect of the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue
headline.print_headline: Jule Campbell, Brains Behind Issue Devoted To Bodies, Dies at 96
